knowledge_graph.merchant_description: "The Activities and Recreation Center is home to a wide range of equipment, exercise studios, specialty fitness areas and more. Join an exercise class, find your own routine in our fitness center, or get personalized advice from a certified trainer. related_questions.question: What activities can you participate in at UC Davis?
related_questions.snippet: Active Campus Recreation members may take as many group exercise, dance, martial arts, and small group training classes as they'd like each quarter with a GX Pass! It's just $35 per quarter or $75 for the academic year.
related_questions.title: Home | Campus Recreation - UC Davis

related_questions.question: Does UC Davis have a recreation center?
related_questions.snippet: UC Davis Campus Recreation Learn about recreational opportunities on campus including the pool, the equestrian center, the craft center and more. Use of the Activities and Recreation Center (ARC) is free of charge to enrolled UC Davis Students.
related_questions.title: Recreation - UC Davis School of Law

related_questions.question: Does UC Davis have a free gym?
related_questions.snippet: Campus Recreation memberships are based on the university's academic calendar; access is therefore granted based on student fees. In other words, your Campus Recreation membership is only active during quarters or semesters in which you are enrolled in classes and paying fees.
related_questions.title: Membership Pricing - UC Davis Campus Recreation

related_questions.question: How to get into the arc at UC Davis?
related_questions.snippet: A valid Campus Recreation membership is required to enter the facility. Members must swipe their Aggie card or scan in utilizing the UC Davis Campus Recreation app. App use is encouraged, Campus Recreation membership cards will only be provided on a case by case basis according to member needs.
